         <OBJECT_CONTRACT ITEM="1">
            <TITLE>
               <P>Provision of Certified Internal Auditor Training</P>
            </TITLE>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="80510000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The Scottish Government (SG) Internal Audit Directorate (IAD) wishes to commission a contractor to provide Certified Internal Auditor (CIA) training in Edinburgh. This will enable an initial cohort of around 24 internal auditors the opportunity to achieve relevant professional accreditation and competence. This will be a single supplier, multiple year framework agreement, with the possibility of extension should an additional cohort of trainees be required. The additional cohort would likely be around 12 further students.</P>
               <P>The contractor will be required to provide a full CIA training programme, including relevant workshop and revision sessions to be delivered in Edinburgh. The contractor will plan the course content, a learning programme and a schedule of delivery; drawing as far as possible on existing core IIA CIA training materials.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="80510000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UK"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The Scottish Government (SG) Internal Audit Directorate (IAD) wishes to commission a contractor to provide Certified Internal Auditor (CIA) training in Edinburgh. This will enable an initial cohort of around 24 internal auditors the opportunity to achieve relevant professional accreditation and competence. This will be a single supplier, multiple year framework agreement, with the possibility of extension should an additional cohort of trainees be required. The additional cohort would likely be around 12 further students.</P>
                  <P>The contractor will be required to provide a full CIA training programme, including relevant workshop and revision sessions to be delivered in Edinburgh. The contractor will plan the course content, a learning programme and a schedule of delivery; drawing as far as possible on existing core IIA CIA training materials.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
            <DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>2018-02-22</DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <CONTRACT_COVERED_GPA/>
         </PROCEDURE>
         <COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
            <INFO_ADD>
               <P>Since 2016, IAD has undergone a period of significant expansion and now provides audit services to a large number of Public Sector clients. The IAD staff count has almost doubled to meet the increased demand for audit services. These new members of staff require a foundation in internal audit theory, methodology and industry best practice. In line with HM Treasury Public Sector Internal Audit Standards (PSIAS), the CIA qualification has been identified as the most suitable course to meet our requirements.</P>
               <P>Potential suppliers will be assessed on the likelihood of the proposed training programme delivering a competent, fully accredited initial cohort within the 3 year timetable. Potential suppliers will be expected to indicate whether they have delivered similar training programmes previously and if so to provide relevant metrics evidencing past performance. The suggested team will also be considered when awarding the framework agreement. Suppliers should be able to demonstrate access to competent course tutors who can understand and communicate the training content to an audience, and who can afford students regular access and appropriate pastoral care.</P>
               <P>NOTE: To register your interest in this notice and obtain any additional information please visit the Public Contracts Scotland Web Site at http://www.publiccontractsscotland.gov.uk/Search/Search_Switch.aspx?ID=528664</P>
               <P>(SC Ref:528664).</P>
            </INFO_ADD>
            <DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE>2018-02-01</DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE>
         </COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
